Observation: {"actions": [{"action_name": "set_temperature", "action_description": "Set the temperature to a specific value", "action_parameters": {"temperature": {"type": "number", "description": "The desired temperature in Fahrenheit", "constraints": {"minimum": 50, "maximum": 90}}}}, {"action_name": "set_mode", "action_description": "Set the thermostat mode", "action_parameters": {"mode": {"type": "string", "description": "The mode to set (e.g., heat, cool, auto)", "constraints": {"allowed_values": ["heat", "cool", "auto"]}}}}]}

Thought: The user wants to set the temperature, so I'll use the "set_temperature" action.
Action: GoogleHomeControlDevice
Action Input: {"device_id": "thermostat-123", "action": "set_temperature", "parameters": {"temperature": 70}}
Observation: {"success": true, "device_status": {"temperature": 70, "mode": "auto", "target_temperature": 70}}

Thought: The thermostat is now set to 70°F. The user asked to set it quickly, so I'll check if there are any other devices that can be controlled quickly.
